body:
hello,
verilator generate the VL_SHIFTL_WWQ function, But the function implementation does not exist.

demo：
```
module  test #(
    parameter EOP_WIDTH = 8,
    parameter DATA_WIDTH = 1024
)
(clk1, head_part0_dly4);
input clk1;
output [DATA_WIDTH-1:0]  head_part0_dly4;
localparam DATA_BYTE = DATA_WIDTH/8;
reg [DATA_WIDTH-1:0]  head_part0_dly4;
wire [DATA_WIDTH-1:0] mpi_head_use_dly4;
wire [EOP_WIDTH-2:0]   sop2_byte_dly4;

always @(posedge clk1) begin
    head_part0_dly4 <= mpi_head_use_dly4 << {(DATA_BYTE - sop2_byte_dly4), 3'd0};
end

endmodule
```

error message :
```
Vtest.cpp :  error: VL_SHIFTL_WWQ was not declared in this scope
    VL_SHIFTL_WWQ(1024,1024,35,__Vtemp1, test__DOOT__mpi_head_use_dly4, 
```

I read the source code ,  the code ' {(DATA_BYTE - sop2_byte_dly4), 3'd0}' should be generate function WWI, but the ‘3'd0’’(left shift)  make IData as QData.
